Mr. Brown is the first white missionary to travel to Umuofia. Mr. Brown institutes a policy of compromise, understanding, and non-aggression between his flock and the clan. He even becomes friends with prominent clansmen and builds a school and a hospital in Umuofia. Unlike Reverend Smith, he attempts to appeal respectfully to the tribeâ€™s value system rather than harshly impose his religion on it.Read anin-depth analysis of Mr. Brown.